      "metadata": null
    },
    {
      "paragraph_name": "UNLOAD",
      "summary": null,
      "purpose": "This step unloads the DBD DBPAUTP0. It executes the IMS program DFSRRC00 with parameters ULU, DFSURGU0, and DBPAUTP0. STEPLIB and DFSRESLB DD statements define the IMS load libraries. IMS DD defines the PSBLIB and DBDLIB libraries. DFSURGU1 defines the output dataset AWS.M2.CARDDEMO.IMSDATA.DBPAUTP0, specifying its disposition, unit, space allocation, and DCB attributes. DDPAUTP0 and DDPAUTX0 define the PAUTHDB and PAUTHDBX datasets. DFSVSAMP defines the DFSVSMDB member in the PROCLIB. DFSCTL contains the SBPARM ACTIV=COND control statement. SYSUDUMP defines the system dump dataset. RECON1, RECON2, and RECON3 define the IMS RECON datasets. DFSWRK01 and DFSSRT01 are dummy datasets. The purpose of this step is to extract the DBD definition into a sequential file for backup or migration purposes.",
      "called_by": [],
      "calls": [],
